\tan(2x)=\frac{\sin(2x)}{\cos(2x)}=\frac{2\sin(x)\cos(x)}{\cos^2(x)-\sin^2(x)}.
\tan(2x)=\frac{2\sin(x)\cos(x)}{\cos^2(x)-\sin^2(x)}=\frac{\qquad\dfrac{2\sin(x)}{\cos(x)}\qquad}{1-\dfrac{\sin^2(x)}{\cos^2(x)}}=\frac{2\tan(x)}{1-\tan^2(x)}.
